14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment directs the
1166 Department of Education to review teacher mentoring programs in public schools in the
1177 State. The review must include, but is not limited to, the number of teachers holding
1188 emergency teacher certificates, conditional teacher certificates and new teacher certificates
1199 with less than 3 years of experience employed at each school administrative unit,
2200 verification that those teachers are assigned mentors, interviews with principals about
2211 mentoring programs and a compilation of descriptions of basic requirements of mentoring
2222 programs throughout the State. The department is required to submit a report to the Joint
2233 Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs based on the findings of the review
2244 no later than February 15, 2026. The committee is authorized to report out legislation
2255 related to the report.
2266 The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
2277 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
